# Wazuh SIEM Installation on Ubuntu Server 22.04

## Overview
This repository documents the step-by-step installation and basic configuration of a **Wazuh SIEM environment on Ubuntu Server 22.04**.  
The goal of this project is to demonstrate how to deploy a basic Security Information and Event Management (SIEM) system for security monitoring, log analysis, and threat detection in a virtualized lab environment.

This project is useful for:
- Cybersecurity students
- SOC analyst learners
- Anyone interested in SIEM deployment and security monitoring

---

# Technologies Used

- Wazuh SIEM
- Ubuntu Server 22.04
- VirtualBox
- Linux command line tools

---

# Lab Environment

The lab environment uses a virtual machine created in VirtualBox.  
Ubuntu Server 22.04 is installed inside the virtual machine and Wazuh is deployed on top of it.

Architecture:

Host Machine  
│  
├── VirtualBox  
│  
└── Ubuntu Server 22.04  
   │  
   └── Wazuh SIEM Platform

---

# Installation Steps Summary

## 1. Download VirtualBox
Download VirtualBox from the official website:

https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads

Install VirtualBox on your host system.

---

## 2. Download Ubuntu
Download Ubuntu installation ISO:

https://ubuntu.com/download/desktop

---

## 3. Create Virtual Machine
After installing VirtualBox:

1. Open VirtualBox
2. Click **New**
3. Give the machine a name
4. Select the Ubuntu ISO image
5. Allocate RAM and storage

---

## 4. Configure Virtual Machine Settings

Before starting the machine, configure the following options:

Settings → General → Advanced

Enable:

- Shared Clipboard
- Drag and Drop

This allows copying files between Windows and Ubuntu.

---

## 5. Install Ubuntu Server
Start the virtual machine and follow the Ubuntu installation wizard.

Basic steps:

- Select language
- Configure keyboard
- Create user account
- Configure disk partition
- Install system packages

Once installation is complete, reboot the system.

---

## 6. Install Wazuh
After Ubuntu installation, install the Wazuh platform on the server.

Wazuh provides:

- Security monitoring
- Log analysis
- Intrusion detection
- Threat intelligence integration

Follow the installation commands provided in the full guide.

---

## 7. Configure Network Access
Ensure the virtual machine has proper network connectivity.

Verify connection using:

ping google.com

Configure network settings if required.

---

## 8. Access Wazuh Dashboard
Once installation is completed, open a web browser and access the Wazuh dashboard.

The dashboard provides:

- Security alerts
- System monitoring
- Log analysis
- Threat detection

---

## 9. Verify Wazuh Services
Check whether Wazuh services are running correctly.

Example verification steps include checking service status and ensuring all components are active.

---

